title: Plane crash sparks DFO explosion
text:
Share on Twitter 
A PLANE has crashed near Essendon Airport in Victoria. 
An aircraft is believed to have clipped a building at the nearby DFO (Direct Factory Outlet) shopping outlet before crashing around 9am on Tuesday morning. 
Witnesses have reported a fiery explosion, and plumes of thick smoke can be scene coming from the scene. 
“There is constant explosions going off, there is black smoke billowing into the sky,” one caller told 3AW on Tuesday. 
Unconfirmed reports suggest the plane was an ambulance aircraft. 
Ambulance and fire crews are responding to the incident. 
Victoria police were working to evacuate the area surrounding the crash site and have advised people to avoid the location. 
The crash has thrown Melbourne traffic into chaos with the Tullamarine Freeway closed in both directions. 
Early witness accounts suggest the aircraft had just taken off and failed to continue its journey. . @theheraldsun nasty stuff. I saw a yellow and red fiery ball explode then black plumes of smoke pic.twitter.com/gDTQESftMv
